{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φείδομαι</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Anacreon Lyricus 101, etc.: \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<i>imperfect</i> φείδοντο (without augment) even in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 716 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] after a diphthong at the end of the preceding line: <i>future</i> φείσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 312 (troch.), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 31a, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>Epic dialect</i> πεφῐδήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.215 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], later <i>future</i> <i>passive</i> in <i>middle</i> sense φ[ε]ισθήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PUniv.Giss.” 21.6 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>aorist 1</i> ἐφεισάμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus 32.1, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 412, 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 2.11, etc.\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>], <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>singular</i> φείσατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.236: _Epic dialect_ reduplicate \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist 2</i> πεφῐδόμην, used by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus in _optative_ πεφῐδοίμην, πεφίδοιτο, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.277, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 20.464 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], <i>infinitive</i> πεφιδέσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 21.101 \">Refs</a>]: <i>perfect</i> <i>participle</i> πεφεισμένος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Hist.Conscr.” 59 (in middle sense, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 50.20)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>imperative</i> πεφίδησο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 14.1363.16 \">Refs</a>]; <i>participle</i> πεφιδημένος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 12.392 \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]:—<b>spare</b>: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <b>spare</b> persons and things, e.g. in war, i.e. <b>not destroy</b> them, with <i>genitive</i>, Τρώων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.101; ἀνδρός 24.158, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.277, 22.54, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 31a; Ἰλίου 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.215; Ἄρης οὐκ ἀγαθῶν φ. 6th c.BC: Anacreon Lyricus [same place]; ἀπ᾽ ἀνδρῶν ὧν Ἄρης ἐφείσατο 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 412; γῆς πατρίδος 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] [same place]; μὴ φείσῃ βίου <b>spare</b> not my life, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 749; μὴ φείδεσθε.. στρατοῦ [prev. author] “Aj.” 844; φ. μήτε ἰδίου μήτε δημοσίου οἰκοδομήματος 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.90, compare 3.74 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>spare, be merciful,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 59. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>spare</b> persons and things in using them, <b>use sparingly,</b> ἵππων φειδόμενος, i. e. <b>taking care</b> of them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.202; πίθου μεσσόθι φ. 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 369 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; φ. ὃν εἶχε βίον (βίον by attraction to the <i>relative</i>) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 908; ἰδίᾳ μὲν τῶν [ὄντων] φείδομαι δημοσίᾳ δὲ λῃτουργῶν ἥδομαι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 21.16; φείδεσθε τοὐλαίου σφόδρα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus Comedy texts 190: in this sense, most frequently with a negative, οὐ φ.\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>] not <b>to spare,</b> i. e. <b>to use</b> or <b>give freely,</b> οὐδέ νυ τοῦ περ [δέπαος] φείσατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.236; μὴ φείδεο σίτου 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 604; θνῄσκωμεν ψυχέων μηκέτι φειδόμενοι 7th c.BC: Tyrtaeus Elegiacus 10.14; τᾶς ζωᾶς [prev. author] 15.5; σφετέρας οὐ φείσατο νευρᾶς 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 6(5).33; φείδεο τῶν νεῶν, μηδὲ ναυμαχίην ποιέο 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.68. ; τούτων φ. μηδενός [prev. author] 9.41, compare 39; φείδοντο κέντρων οὐδέν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 716; οὐδὲν φ. αὐτῶν οὔτ᾽ ἐν πόνοις κτλ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 4.2.1, compare 7.1.29; οὔτε τοῦ σώματος οὔτε τῶν ὄντων 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 2.11; οὐδενὸς ἂν ἐφείσατο τῶν ἑαυτοῦ 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 19.24; οὔθ᾽ ἱερῶν κτεάνων οὔτε τι δημοσίων φ. 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus 4.13; μήτε χρημάτων μήτε πόνων 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 78a: later also with _accusative_, τῶν συμμάχων and τὰ τῶν συμμάχων both in 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 50.20. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>to be sparing, live thriftily,</b> φείδεσθαι μὲν ἄμεινον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 931; τοὺς φειδομένους καὶ τοὺς ἀκριβῶς διαιτῶντας 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.32; οἱ γεωργοῦντες καὶ φ. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 24.172, compare 5th c.BC: Antipho Sophista 53 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; frequently in <i>participle</i> φειδόμενος, η, ον, <b>thrifty,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 247, 553 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], etc.; ὄμμασι φειδομένοις with <b>shrinking, shy</b> eyes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 12.21 (2nd c.AD: Strato Epigrammaticus), compare 5.215 (6th c.AD: Agathias Historicus et Epigrammaticus), 268 ([prev. author])\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; αἱ μὴ φ. (i.e. μέλισσαι) the un<b>thrifty</b> ones, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 627a20: also ἔπαινοι πάνυ πεφεισμένοι 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Hist.Conscr.” 59; πεφιδημένα δάκτυλα 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 12.392 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; compare πεφεισμένως, φειδομένως. <br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>have consideration for,</b> τῆς τοῦ λόγου συμμετρίας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.114b \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: with <i>negative</i>, <b>pay</b> no <b>heed to,</b> οὔτ᾽ ἀνθρώπων φείδεται οὔτε θεῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 5.278 (6th c.AD: Paulus Silentiarius Epigrammaticus), compare 7.706 (4th c.BC: Diogenes Cynicus Philosophus). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>draw back from, refrain from,</b> θαλάσσας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 4.13 (probably); κελεύθου 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 9.20; κινδύνου 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.5.18; τᾶς θήρας 2nd c.BC: Bion Bucolicus “fragment” 10.12 \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; τοῦ λέγειν, τοῦ ἀκολουθεῖν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.6.19 (variant), “HG” 7.1.24; φείδου μηδὲν ὧνπερ ἐννοεῖς 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 115, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 401, etc.; οὐδενὸς φεισάμενος οὔτε τῶν πρὸς τοὺς θεοὺς οὔτε τῶν πρὸς τοὺς πολίτας δικαίων “SIG” 708.36 (Istropolis, 2nd c.BC): (_absolutely_, μὴ φείδεσθε 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 1285; φείδου μηδέν [prev. author] “Hec.” 1044; μὴ φείδου, εἴ τι ἔχεις διδάσκειν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.6.35)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>spare</b> to do, <b>forbear</b> from doing, uncertain in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 393 (perhaps _absolutely_, post φείδου δ᾽ distinguendum)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also φ. μή τι δρᾶσαι τῶν τυραννικῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 574b; τί φειδόμεσθα τῶν λίθων.. μὴ οὐ καταξαίνειν τὸν ἄνδρ; 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 319 (troch.). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX, with Preps., φ. ἐπί τινι \">Refs</a>]<b>have mercy upon.., </b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Jer.15.5, 21.7; ἐπί τινα [prev. author] 28(51).3 \">LXX</a>]; φ. περί τινος <b>to keep one's hands off</b>.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.2Ki.12.6 (but φ. περὶ κακώσεως\">LXX</a>] <b>spare</b> to hurt, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.Sir.13.12); φ. ὑπὲρ τῆς κολοκύνθης LXX.Jonah.4.10; ἀπό τινος LXX.1Ki.15.3, LXX.Eze.24.21 \">LXX</a>]; φ. τι ἀπό τινος <b>keep</b> it <b>off, Jb.</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 30.10 \">Refs</a>]; φ. τῆς ψυχῆς ἀπὸ θανάτου[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 33.18, cf. LXX.Psa.18(19).14 \">LXX</a>]; φειδεύμενοι (from <i>contraction</i> φειδέομαι) is conjecture for φιλεύμεναι in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Eusebius Myndius Philosophus 17. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5339","accentedUnicode":"φείδομαι","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0857","matchingForm":"ἀφειδία","stepTransliteration":"afeidia","gloss":"unsparing","_zh_tw_Gloss":"苦待","_es_Gloss":"trato severo","_zh_Gloss":"苦待"},{"strongNumber":"G5340","matchingForm":"φειδομένως","stepTransliteration":"feidomenōs","gloss":"sparingly","_zh_tw_Gloss":"小量","_es_Gloss":"escasamente","_zh_Gloss":"小量"}],"shortDef":"to spare, refrain from","mediumDef":"to spare, refrain from <br /><b>to spare; to be tender of,</b> <ref='Rom.8.32'>Rom. 8:32;</ref> <b>to spare,</b> in respect of hard dealing, <ref='Act.20.29'>Acts 20:29;</ref> <ref='Rom.11.21'>Rom. 11:21;</ref> <ref='1Co.7.28'>1Cor. 7:28;</ref> <ref='2Co.1.23'>2Cor. 1:23;</ref> 13:2; <ref='2Pe.2.4'>2Pet. 2:4</ref>, 5; <i>absolute</i> <b>to forbear, abstain, refrain</b> <ref='2Co.12.6'>2Cor. 12:6</ref>*","stepGloss":"to spare","stepTransliteration":"feidomai","count":10,"_es_Definition":"escatimar, reservar ; abstenerse de, evitar hacer (algo)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 免除, 手下留情<br>2) 節制, 避開 (林後 12:6)","_zh_Definition":"1) 免除, 手下留情<br>2) 节制, 避开 (林后 12:6)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"tiếc; tùng.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"愛惜","_es_Gloss":"escatimar","_zh_Gloss":"爱惜"}]}